reviews.review_text:
I really wasn't But I wish I were
He's Gone seems to be for Brent
Hornsby is Terrific

Going where the wind don't blow so strange Very nice sound here..I attended this night and the night before..I love NYC! The smell of piss and pure mayhem in the air!! The 1st set is solid but the 2nd set smokes! Haunting China Doll!! so please>GIVE IT A WHIRL>Forever Grateful>Forever Dead!!!!!!

Twas in another lifetime 26 years later and my conclusion stays the same as when I walked out of MSG......... Jerry and Bruce rocked.  Jerry's tune selection was stellar other than FOTD.   Bobby's tune selection was "meh"....  Put it all together and you get 4 stars....  Yes, a super charged Jerry more than made up for Little Red Rooster, Promised Land [sorry, but it was sooooo overplayed], Spoonful and the obligatory One More Saturday Night......   This was one of those nights where it was less about what they played and all about how they played.  And on this night, Jerry played his heart out.
